The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

THE DVD 

 (Landmark, Rs 599) Michael Jackson tries to prove why he calls himself the 

King of Pop in this live concert promoting the album Dangerous. The 16-song 

set includes classics like Beat It, Billy Jean and Smooth Criminal, 

as well as hits from the new album, like Black or White and Heal the 

World. 

THE FILM

 (Nandan, 6.30 pm, October 21) Directed by Olivier Ducastel and Jacques Martineau, 

the film deals with the quest for true love. Jeanne meets her perfect man in the 

HIV-positive Olivier. Presented by The French Association.

THE LAUNCH

 (Taj 

Bengal, 7.30 pm, October 17) Penguin Books India and Taj Bengal present the launch 

of Two Lives by Vikram Seth at Crystal Hall at 7.30 pm on Monday. The author 

will read from the book, a semi-biographical account of his uncle and aunt. 




